planning to spend a longer time in china then you may want to consider learning some of the traditional arts. traveling to china is after all a unique chance to learn the basics, or refine already acquired skills, directly from master practitioners in the arts' home country. many cities have academies that accept beginners, and not knowing chinese is usually not a problem as you can learn by example and imitation. calligraphy (书法 shūfǎ), a term that covers both writing characters and painting scrolls (that is, classical landscapes and the like) remains a popular national hobby. many calligraphers practice by 